B2C Commerce Order Bundle Data Mappings

The B2C Commerce Order Bundle shows a sample of the key mappings organized by source objects. You can view all the mappings by reviewing your data streams after the bundle is deployed.

When ingesting a bundle, these source objects are automatically mapped to DMOs. Find information about individual fields and specific relationships in the reference link related to that object.

SOURCE OBJECT	DESCRIPTION	MAPPING REFERENCE
Bundles Product	The Bundles Product object represents products that can be purchased as a group. Bundle products can contain independent inventory records for the bundle and the product that make up the bundle.	Bundles Product Mapping
Goods Product	The Goods Product object represents hard goods that can be purchased.	Goods Product Mapping
Master Product	The Master Product object is a container for some types of products. Master products don’t have inventory records.	Master Product Mapping
Product Catalog	The Product Catalog object represents categories and products used to organize merchandise.	Product Catalog Mapping
Product Category	The Product Category object represents categories of products.	Product Category Mapping
Product Category Product	The Product Category Product object represents categories of products.	Product Category Product Mapping
Sales Order	The Sales Order object represents an order.	Sales Order Mapping
Sales Order Customer	The Sales Order Customer object represents a customer making an order. 	Sales Order Customer Mapping
Sales Order Product	The Sales Order Product object represents an order.	Sales Order Product Mapping
NOTE Where possible, we changed noninclusive terms to align with our company value of Equality. We retained noninclusive terms to document a third-party system, but we encourage the developer community to embrace more inclusive language. We can update the term when it’s no longer required for technical accuracy.
